radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bilateral peripheral pulmonary artery stenoses (narrowing of the proximal left pulmonary artery and the upper lobe branch of the right pulmonary artery), small patent ductus arteriosus, and normal biventricular function.

Moderate increase in pulmonary artery pressures (mean PA pressure = 43 mm Hg) with a systolic pressure gradient of 22 mm Hg between the right pulmonary artery and the right upper lobe pulmonary artery.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Repeat catheterization confirmed mild pulmonary artery stenosis.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal right coronary artery with retrograde filling of the left coronary system via collaterals from the right coronary artery.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Indicator of congenital origin ostial stenosis, though no evidence of atherosclerosis and calcification.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Complete absence of antegrade flow in the left coronary artery.
Normal renal arteries with no evidence of renal artery involvement.
